---
title: Sliced Steak Tagliata with Roasted Potatoes, Sugar Snap Peas, and Tomato Vinaigrette
description: *Tagliata* comes from the Italian word for “to cut,” referring to the fact that this steak is always served sliced. Legend even has it that the dish originated with a particularly persnickety aristocrat who demanded that her servants do the carving for her. We’re honoring her request by slicing up sirloin before serving and drizzling it with a balsamic sauce, which dribbles onto the potato wedges, soaking them in succulent juices.
